---
title: BeaconLink Failover Sequence
---

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant Runtime as Runtime Platform
    participant Agent as BeaconLink Agent
    participant Relay as Relay Network
    participant Control as BeaconLink Control Plane
    participant Inventory as Inventory Service
    participant Policy as Policy Engine
    participant Scheduler as Distributed Scheduler
    participant Planner as Deployment Planner
    participant Workflow as Workflow Engine
    participant Target as Standby BeaconLink Agent
    participant Events as Event Streaming Platform
    participant Audit as Audit Service

    %% =====================================================
    %% Normal Operation
    %% =====================================================

    Note over Agent,Control: Workload is healthy and continuously reconciled

    loop Regular Heartbeats

        Agent->>Relay: Heartbeat
        Relay->>Control: Forward heartbeat

        Control->>Inventory: Update health
        Inventory-->>Control: Health recorded

    end

    %% =====================================================
    %% Failure Detection
    %% =====================================================

    Runtime-->>Agent: Runtime failure detected

    Agent->>Relay: Failure notification

    Relay->>Control: Forward failure event

    Control->>Events: Publish RuntimeFailureDetected

    Control->>Audit: Record runtime failure

    %% =====================================================
    %% Health Verification
    %% =====================================================

    Control->>Inventory: Retrieve latest health

    Inventory-->>Control: Current agent status

    Control->>Policy: Verify failover policy

    Policy-->>Control: Failover permitted

    %% =====================================================
    %% Failure Classification
    %% =====================================================

    alt Recoverable Failure

        Control->>Workflow: Restart workload

        Workflow->>Agent: Execute restart

        Agent->>Runtime: Restart workload

        Runtime-->>Agent: Restart successful

        Agent->>Control: Recovery completed

        Control->>Events: Publish WorkloadRecovered

    else Node Failure

        Control->>Scheduler: Remove failed capacity

        Scheduler->>Inventory: Refresh cluster capacity

        Inventory-->>Scheduler: Updated inventory

        Scheduler-->>Control: Failed node isolated

    end

    %% =====================================================
    %% Failover Planning
    %% =====================================================

    Control->>Planner: Generate failover plan

    Planner->>Inventory: Discover healthy standby agents

    Inventory-->>Planner: Candidate execution nodes

    Planner->>Planner: Evaluate capabilities
    Planner->>Planner: Select optimal target

    Planner-->>Control: Failover execution plan

    %% =====================================================
    %% Target Selection
    %% =====================================================

    Control->>Scheduler: Reserve standby capacity

    Scheduler-->>Control: Capacity reserved

    Control->>Workflow: Create failover workflow

    %% =====================================================
    %% Workload Migration
    %% =====================================================

    Workflow->>Target: Dispatch deployment

    Target->>Target: Validate desired state

    Target->>Target: Retrieve immutable revision

    Target->>Target: Prepare runtime

    Target->>Runtime: Deploy workload

    loop Deployment Progress

        Runtime-->>Target: Progress update

        Target->>Workflow: Status update

        Workflow->>Events: Publish FailoverProgress

    end

    %% =====================================================
    %% Validation
    %% =====================================================

    Runtime-->>Target: Deployment successful

    Target->>Runtime: Execute health checks

    Runtime-->>Target: Workload healthy

    Target->>Inventory: Update workload ownership

    Inventory-->>Target: Inventory synchronized

    %% =====================================================
    %% Traffic Recovery
    %% =====================================================

    Workflow->>Control: Failover complete

    Control->>Events: Publish FailoverCompleted

    Control->>Audit: Record successful failover

    Note over Control,Target: Traffic is directed to the<br/>new execution node through the<br/>Relay Network and runtime routing.

    %% =====================================================
    %% Failed Node Recovery
    %% =====================================================

    opt Original Node Returns

        Agent->>Relay: Reconnect

        Relay->>Control: Agent online

        Control->>Policy: Validate identity

        Policy-->>Control: Authorized

        Control->>Inventory: Mark node healthy

        Inventory-->>Control: Capacity restored

        Scheduler->>Inventory: Re-enable scheduling

        Control->>Events: Publish AgentRecovered

    end

    %% =====================================================
    %% Continuous Reconciliation
    %% =====================================================

    loop Ongoing Reconciliation

        Target->>Control: Heartbeat

        Control->>Inventory: Verify desired state

        Control->>Policy: Continuous authorization

        alt Drift Detected

            Control->>Workflow: Trigger reconciliation

            Workflow->>Events: Publish DriftDetected

        else State Healthy

            Control->>Events: Publish WorkloadHealthy

        end

    end

    Note over Workflow,Target: BeaconLink automatically restores service by<br/>combining failure detection, policy validation,<br/>capability-based scheduling, immutable deployments,<br/>and Continuous Reconciliation.